## Task Tracking — Mandatory Post-Completion Update

### Rule

After completing **any non-trivial task** (bug fix, feature, refactor, docs update, audit, etc.), you **MUST** update `tasks/todo.md` before declaring the work done.

### When to Update

- A multi-step task finishes (3+ steps or involving multiple files)
- A plan-mode plan is fully executed
- A skill workflow completes (e.g., quality audit, dependency sweep, e2e-testing)
- A user-requested change is applied and verified

### What to Update

1. **Move completed items** from "Current Tasks" to "Completed" with a date stamp:
   ```
   ### <Task Title> (Completed: YYYY-MM-DD)
   - [x] Item description
   ```
2. **Remove or clear** "Current Tasks" entries that are done.
3. **Add verification results** if applicable (test pass/fail, lint status, etc.).

### What NOT to Do

- Do not update `tasks/todo.md` for trivial single-file edits (typo fix, one-line change).
- Do not remove the "Completed" history — it serves as an audit trail.
- Do not modify `tasks/lessons.md` here; that file is updated only on agent corrections.

### Format Reference

```markdown
## Current Tasks

- [ ] Active task description

---

## Completed

### Task Name (Completed: 2026-02-19)

- [x] Completed item 1
- [x] Completed item 2
```

### Enforcement

This rule is checked as the **final step** of every task execution. Skipping it is a violation of the workflow orchestration rules.
